 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Sr. System Engineer NVIDIA 237 reviews Sunnyvale, CA NVIDIA 237 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description We are looking for an experienced Solutions Engineer (Sr SE) based in Sunnyvale, CA. As part of our Business Development and end-user sales, you will be responsible for driving our end-to-end technology solutions with some of our most strategic web 2.0, cloud and enterprise data center customers, as well as for identifying gaps in business technology and offering recommendations to our marketing and engineering teams on our product strategy. 
 
 What you'll be doing:
 Finding new business opportunities for Mellanox products and technology solutions in cloud, artificial intelligence and big data applications and works closely with the R&D, Product Marketing and Sales teams to make our customers dreams a reality.
 Technical account management for Mellanox key web 2.0 and cloud data center customers
 Conducting regular customer meetings for product updates and introductions to new technology solutions
 Preparing and delivering product roadmap presentations to customers and technology partners -
 Responding to RFP/RFI proposals for network, security and storage designs
 Building and delivering custom-tailored product demonstrations and POCs for solutions that address critical business needs for our customers
 Technical project management of complex networking deployments and design-in opportunities
 Analyzing and troubleshooting performance issues with the new technology at the customer site
 Preparing and delivering technical training presentations
 
 What we need to see:
 Self-motivated, results-oriented individual with the inspiration and skills to drive the technical pre-sales process.
 Technical degree or equivalent experience and have 5-7 years of Solution Engineering (aka Systems or Sales Engineering) experience
 Data center engineering, networking, or cloud application
 Must have strong sense of achievement and customer focused attitude
 Understanding of system level issues, including Operating Systems, Linux kernel drivers, PCIe devices, NICs, and hardware architecture
 Deep networking experience, including solid knowledge of L2/L3 Ethernet or other networking protocols
 Technical presentations & architectural design
 Confidence developing Proofs-of-Concept
 Effective in managing their time and capable of handling multiple demands and competing deadlines
 Experience with leading and managing technical teams is a plus
 Ability to travel up to 20%
